foreDsx1.description: MIB module for supporting the DSX1 port module.

dsx1ForeConfTable.name: dsx1ForeConfTable
dsx1ForeConfTable.description: A table of DSX1 switch port configuration information.

dsx1ForeConfEntry.name: dsx1ForeConfEntry
dsx1ForeConfEntry.description: A table entry containing DSX1 configuration information for each port. Not all RFC1406 configuration table variables are included, and some are modified.

dsx1ForeLineIndex.name: dsx1ForeLineIndex
dsx1ForeLineIndex.description: This object is the identifier of a DS1 Inter- face on a managed device. If there is an ifEn- try that is directly associated with this and only this DS1 interface, it should have the same value as ifIndex. Otherwise, the value exceeds ifNumber, and is a unique identifier following this rule: inside interfaces (e.g., equipment side) with even numbers and outside interfaces (e.g., network side) with odd numbers.

dsx1ForeReceiveCode.name: dsx1ForeReceiveCode
dsx1ForeReceiveCode.description: This variable indicates the type of code that was received across the DSX interface. The values mean: dsx1ReceiveNoCode receiving looped or normal data dsx1ReceiveLineCode receiving request for a line loopback dsx1ReceivePayloadCode receiving a request for a payload loopback dsx1ReceiveResetCode receiving a loopback deactivation request dsx1ReceiveQRS receiving a Quasi-Random Signal (QRS) test pattern dsx1Receive511Pattern receiving a 511 bit fixed test pattern dsx1Receive3in24Pattern receiving a fixed test pattern of 3 bits set in 24 dsx1ReceiveTestPattern receiving a test pattern other than the above.

dsx1ForeLineLength.name: dsx1ForeLineLength
dsx1ForeLineLength.description: This variable represents the length of the physical cable connected to the dsx1 port. The user has to set this object to match the physical cable in order to get the netmod to receive the signal on the cable. The different values are: dsx1LineLt40 (1) means the line is shorter than 40m, dsx1Line40-80 (2) means the line length is between 40m and 80m, dsx1Line80-120 (3) means the line length is between 80m and 120m, dsx1Line120-160 (4) means the line length is between 120m and 160m, dsx1Line160-200 (5) means the line length is between 160m and 200m, dsx1LineE1Coax (6) means E1 Coax line, not applicable for T1, dsx1LineTwistedPair (7) means E1 Twisted Pair line, not applicable for T1.

dsx1ForeFdlConfiguration.name: dsx1ForeFdlConfiguration
dsx1ForeFdlConfiguration.description: This varialbe indicate whether the FDL state machine acts as network or user side

dsx1ForeLineImpedance.name: dsx1ForeLineImpedance
dsx1ForeLineImpedance.description: The default line impedance of the E1 line. Note that this is not applicable for T1

dsx1ForeFdlPerfConf.name: dsx1ForeFdlPerfConf
dsx1ForeFdlPerfConf.description: This variable indicate whether the FDL state machine is enabled or turned off for performance reports. See T1.403 for details.

dsx1ForeFdlBomConf.name: dsx1ForeFdlBomConf
dsx1ForeFdlBomConf.description: This variable indicate whether Bit Oriented Messages will be generated and transmitted. See T1.403 for details.

dsx1ForeUpStreamAIS.name: dsx1ForeUpStreamAIS
dsx1ForeUpStreamAIS.description: The upsteam AIS alarm generation flag enabled: the upstream AIS is generated disabled: the upstream AIS is not generated

dsx1ForePortModel.name: dsx1ForePortModel
dsx1ForePortModel.description: The underlying hardware port model. The value corresponds to the hwPortModel mib variable.

dsx1ForeAdminStatus.name: dsx1ForeAdminStatus
dsx1ForeAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all interfaces start with adminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, adminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

dsx1ForeFramingTable.name: dsx1ForeFramingTable
dsx1ForeFramingTable.description: A table of DSX1 framing statistics information.

dsx1ForeFramingEntry.name: dsx1ForeFramingEntry
dsx1ForeFramingEntry.description: A table entry containing DSX1 framing statistics information.

dsx1ForeFramingLOSs.name: dsx1ForeFramingLOSs
dsx1ForeFramingLOSs.description: The number of secondsx in which Loss Of Signal (LOS) errors have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingLCVs.name: dsx1ForeFramingLCVs
dsx1ForeFramingLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCV) that have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingFERRs.name: dsx1ForeFramingFERRs
dsx1ForeFramingFERRs.description: The number of Framing ERRor (FERR) events that have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingOOFs.name: dsx1ForeFramingOOFs
dsx1ForeFramingOOFs.description: The number of Out Of Frame (OOF) error events that have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingAISs.name: dsx1ForeFramingAISs
dsx1ForeFramingAISs.description: The number of secondsx in which Alarm Indication Signals (AIS) have been detected. AIS indicates that an upstream failure has been detected by the far end.

dsx1ForeFramingB8ZSPatterns.name: dsx1ForeFramingB8ZSPatterns
dsx1ForeFramingB8ZSPatterns.description: The number of seconds in which B8ZS Pattern events have been detected.

dsx1ForeFraming8Zeros.name: dsx1ForeFraming8Zeros
dsx1ForeFraming8Zeros.description: The number of seconds in which 8 Zeros events have been detected.

dsx1ForeFraming16Zeros.name: dsx1ForeFraming16Zeros
dsx1ForeFraming16Zeros.description: The number of seconds in which 16 Zeros events have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingYellowAlarms.name: dsx1ForeFramingYellowAlarms
dsx1ForeFramingYellowAlarms.description: The number of secondsx in which Yellow Alarm events have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingRedAlarms.name: dsx1ForeFramingRedAlarms
dsx1ForeFramingRedAlarms.description: The number of secondsx in which Red Alarm events have been detected.

dsx1ForeFramingBEEs.name: dsx1ForeFramingBEEs
dsx1ForeFramingBEEs.description: The number of Bit Encoding Error (BEE) events that have been detected.

dsx1ForeAtmTable.name: dsx1ForeAtmTable
dsx1ForeAtmTable.description: A table of DSX1 ATM statistics information.

dsx1ForeAtmEntry.name: dsx1ForeAtmEntry
dsx1ForeAtmEntry.description: A table entry containing DSX1 ATM statistics information.

dsx1ForeAtmIndex.name: dsx1ForeAtmIndex
dsx1ForeAtmIndex.description: The ifIndex of this port, actually it's currently the ifIndex of the associaated dsx1 port not the ATM port as currently they are assumed to be the same thing which of course they are not

dsx1ForeAtmRxCells.name: dsx1ForeAtmRxCells
dsx1ForeAtmRxCells.description: Number of ATM cells that were received.

dsx1ForeAtmTxCells.name: dsx1ForeAtmTxCells
dsx1ForeAtmTxCells.description: Number of non-null ATM cells that were transmitted.
